WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.160
Here is the bridge between the lab and the field.

2
00:00:02.260 --> 00:00:04.743
Real numbers you measure at the bench flow straight into

3
00:00:04.843 --> 00:00:07.188
the same physics that predicts erosion in the desert.

4
00:00:07.966 --> 00:00:11.775
How dense is the culture? How much glutamate are we feeding? How salty

5
00:00:11.875 --> 00:00:15.180
is the water? These are dials you actually turn on the bench.

6
00:00:15.266 --> 00:00:18.769
Every one of those bench inputs feeds the exact same wind-erosion

7
00:00:18.869 --> 00:00:22.428
model the other modules use — no separate, hand-waved lab version.

8
00:00:22.500 --> 00:00:25.014
And the answer shows up as a virtual dune — hold

9
00:00:25.114 --> 00:00:28.173
the settings that give a strong crust, and it stands firm.

10
00:00:28.266 --> 00:00:30.810
Turn a dial the wrong way — too much salt, too

11
00:00:30.910 --> 00:00:33.798
little feed — and you watch the same dune wear down.

12
00:00:33.898 --> 00:00:37.361
An experiment on Monday becomes a field prediction on Tuesday.

